1. Bitcoin spot ETF had a total net inflow of 11.7984 million US dollars yesterday, and continued to have net inflow for 4 days;
2. Ethereum spot ETF had a total net outflow of 11.7459 million US dollars yesterday, and continued to have net outflow for 11 days;
3. Arthur Hayes: BTC may have bottomed out, but US stocks may still have room to fall;
4. WLFI is suspected of testing the transfer function and transferring nearly 200 million tokens to a certain address;
5. The Federal Reserve has raised the threshold for interest rate cuts, and inflation expectations have been raised twice in a row;
6. Pudgy Penguins CEO: The income from staking ETH through fat penguin NFT is better than directly staking ETH;
7. Coinbase released the Ethereum validator performance report, and the number of validators reached 120,000;
8. RedStone clarified: It has not cooperated with Web3Port or Whisper;
9. A whale recharged 7.37 million US dollars of USDC to HyperLiquid within 16 hours and bought 400,000 HYPE;
10. The repurchase progress of SHELL market makers reached 74%, and the balance of the repurchase address increased to 19.95 million.
